{
  "texts": [
    "It considers supervised learning techniques and is used in many academic disciplines to look for input patterns that haven't been found before (JayaLakshmi and Kishore, 2022).",
    "The features of the tagged images must be extracted using a substantial amount of data for training (Noor et al., 2020).",
    "Qiu et al. (2020) predicted the subjects' cognitive function using a deep neural network (DNN) based on the subjects' age and blood test items.",
    "To train the DNN model, they recruited 202 individuals with a range of systemic metabolic diseases.",
    "The Mini-Mental State Examination (MMSE) was administered to the participants."
  ]
}